The paper deals with an algorithmic study of a graph augmentation problem, which involves finding a superposition of two given graphs that increases the connectivity of one of them. This problem is related to graph theory, combinatorics, and computational complexity. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Additionally, the paper involves optimization problems and polynomial time algorithms, which suggest the sub-categories cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
